race.comment: HORRIBLE HANK (3) has two wins from two starts this prep, both north of the border. Settled a long way back then flew home to score last start over 1200m at Chinchilla. This is a shade tougher but he is an honest sprinter who looks sure to measure up again. SMILING AMOS (5) encountered a soft track for the first time last start and was an abject failure. Hasn't won for a very long while but his form earlier this campaign was encouraging. Worth another chance. VISUALISE (9) returns from a 20-week spell. Opened last preparation with a dominant all-the-way win over 1400m at Glen Innes. Not seen at the trials so let the betting tell the story. MASTER GEE (10) was back in form last start when a close second over 1000m at Tamworth. His winning strike rate doesn't inspire confidence but with Bullock to ride for the first time he might surprise. KOOL BRUCE (12) won a lowly maiden first-up at Inverell. Harder here but can sneak into the minor end of the prize.
